<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="ida9361344-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5" identifier="/us/usc/t10/s2184"><num value="2184">§ 2184.</num><heading> Termination of assistance</heading>
<chapeau style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">Assistance under this chapter—</chapeau><paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="ida9361345-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5" identifier="/us/usc/t10/s2184/1"><num value="1">(1)</num><content> shall be discontinued for any person whose conduct or progress is unsatisfactory under standards consistent with those established under <ref href="/us/usc/t38/s3524">section 3524 of title 38</ref>; and</content>
</paragraph>
<paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="ida9361346-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5" identifier="/us/usc/t10/s2184/2"><num value="2">(2)</num><content> may not be provided for any person for more than 45 months (or the equivalent in other than full-time education or training).</content>
</paragraph>
<sourceCredit id="ida9361347-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5">(Added <ref href="/us/pl/99/399/tVIII/s806/d/1">Pub. L. 99–399, title VIII, § 806(d)(1)</ref>, <date date="1986-08-27">Aug. 27, 1986</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/100/888">100 Stat. 888</ref>; amended <ref href="/us/pl/103/337/dA/tX/s1070/e/7">Pub. L. 103–337, div. A, title X, § 1070(e)(7)</ref>, <date date="1994-10-05">Oct. 5, 1994</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/108/2859">108 Stat. 2859</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
<notes type="uscNote" id="ida9361348-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5">
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" role="crossHeading" topic="editorialNotes" id="ida9361349-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"><heading class="centered"><b>Editorial Notes</b></heading></note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" topic="amendments" id="ida936134a-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Amendments</heading><p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">1994—Par. (1). <ref href="/us/pl/103/337">Pub. L. 103–337</ref> substituted “3524” for “1724”.</p>
</note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" role="crossHeading" topic="statutoryNotes" id="ida936134b-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"><heading class="centered"><b>Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries</b></heading></note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" topic="effectiveDate" id="ida936134c-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Effective Date</heading><p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">Section applicable with respect to persons whose captive status begins after <date date="1981-01-21">Jan. 21, 1981</date>, see <ref href="/us/pl/99/399/s806/d/3">section 806(d)(3) of Pub. L. 99–399</ref>, set out as a note under 2181 of this title.</p>
</note>
